The word DIME literally means "one-tenth".  It's related etymologically to "decimal", and it is one of the four actual units of currency in the US; the main unit is the dollar, one-tenth of which is a dime;, one-hundredth of a dollar is a cent, and one-thousandth of a dollar is a mil, which we only consider at the gasoline pump, when the price is, say, $2.999.

Penny, nickel and quarter are all just the names of the coins, not their values.

